subsection.p:
Suppose a garden path has boundary r=\frac{\theta}{2\pi}, \qquad 0\le\theta\le2\pi. The region inside one turn of the spiral is 0\le\theta\le2\pi, \qquad 0\le r\le \frac{\theta}{2\pi}. Its area is
A \amp= \int_0^{2\pi} \int_0^{\theta/(2\pi)} r\,dr\,d\theta \amp= \int_0^{2\pi} \frac12\left(\frac{\theta}{2\pi}\right)^2 d\theta \amp= \frac{1}{8\pi^2} \left[ \frac{\theta^3}{3} \right]_0^{2\pi} \amp= \frac{1}{8\pi^2}\cdot\frac{8\pi^3}{3} \amp= \frac{\pi}{3}.
So \boxed{ A=\frac{\pi}{3}. }

